WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:08.458 --> 00:00:09.791
Mr Holmes…

2
00:00:17.541 --> 00:00:18.684
Mother?

3
00:00:18.708 --> 00:00:20.125
Stand back from the door.

4
00:00:22.208 --> 00:00:24.291
Sherlock. you're in trouble. darling?

5
00:00:30.541 --> 00:00:31.726
What a good idea.

6
00:00:31.750 --> 00:00:32.750
Sit down.

7
00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:37.892
"The man with the bird's claw."

8
00:00:37.916 --> 00:00:40.142
- Did you say those words to anyone else?
- No.

9
00:00:40.166 --> 00:00:42.934
You didn't tell anyone
apart from me and mycroft?

10
00:00:42.958 --> 00:00:46.416
I tried to tell you. He's
coming back for me.

11
00:00:47.000 --> 00:00:48.101
Who's he?

12
00:00:48.125 --> 00:00:49.791
They're listening.

13
00:00:51.541 --> 00:00:52.601
The whirring.

14
00:00:52.625 --> 00:00:54.541
Always the whirring.

15
00:00:56.875 --> 00:00:59.708
I-I couldn't understand
why you wouldn't believe me.

16
00:01:01.000 --> 00:01:07.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

17
00:01:10.541 --> 00:01:11.708
Can you hear it now?

18
00:01:22.791 --> 00:01:23.851
I do.

19
00:01:23.875 --> 00:01:25.541
I hear it.

20
00:01:32.416 --> 00:01:33.708
Sherlock.

21
00:01:36.458 --> 00:01:37.958
What in god's name…

22
00:01:40.166 --> 00:01:41.250
What fun.

23
00:01:55.666 --> 00:01:57.875
What is it?

24
00:01:59.083 --> 00:02:00.833
Some sort of listening device.

25
00:02:05.541 --> 00:02:07.250
You were right. mother.

26
00:02:09.333 --> 00:02:11.625
Someone has been recording you.

27
00:02:13.250 --> 00:02:15.041
Open the door!

28
00:02:15.500 --> 00:02:17.809
Time to leave.

29
00:02:17.833 --> 00:02:19.125
Open up!

30
00:02:23.333 --> 00:02:25.309
- Mr Holmes!
- Wait.

31
00:02:33.250 --> 00:02:34.517
Sherlock.

32
00:02:48.416 --> 00:02:49.708
Shall we take the floor?

33
00:02:54.291 --> 00:02:58.791
Now. I never was very good
at this. You did try to teach me.

34
00:03:00.083 --> 00:03:03.309
- You always had two left feet.
- Still do.

35
00:03:03.333 --> 00:03:05.642
- One. two. three. One. two. three.
- One. two. three.

36
00:03:05.666 --> 00:03:08.291
One. two. three. One. two. three.

37
00:03:08.916 --> 00:03:10.791
Look at me. mother. Just us.

38
00:03:11.333 --> 00:03:14.041
You. me. and the music.

39
00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:52.416
See how you like it.

40
00:03:55.000 --> 00:03:57.125
I think he liked it.

41
00:04:04.833 --> 00:04:07.625
Are we making an escape?

42
00:04:09.291 --> 00:04:10.934
Yes.

43
00:04:10.958 --> 00:04:12.601
Stop! Thief!

44
00:05:12.708 --> 00:05:15.750
Get out of here!

45
00:05:19.791 --> 00:05:22.250
You've got an appointment. Princess.

46
00:05:42.916 --> 00:05:44.267
Two bushels.

47
00:05:44.291 --> 00:05:45.517
What?

48
00:05:45.541 --> 00:05:48.142
Your weight. Just approximate.

49
00:05:48.166 --> 00:05:49.375
For the drop.

50
00:05:50.250 --> 00:05:53.058
Because if the rope's too
short. then your neck won't snap.

51
00:05:53.082 --> 00:05:54.642
and then you'll be left slowly choking.

52
00:05:55.416 --> 00:05:56.976
It's a rather undignified way

53
00:05:57.000 --> 00:05:59.226
to shuffle off this mortal
coil. wouldn't you agree?

54
00:05:59.250 --> 00:06:02.541
"Eight stone. I'd guess. 7'10" drop.

55
00:06:03.708 --> 00:06:06.726
Did you know that the first
account of execution by hanging

56
00:06:06.750 --> 00:06:08.017
is in homer's odyssey?

57
00:06:08.041 --> 00:06:10.184
No. I did not know that. sir. Fascinating.

58
00:06:10.208 --> 00:06:12.351
Is this supposed to intimidate me?

59
00:06:12.375 --> 00:06:13.809
No. it's supposed to kill you.

60
00:06:13.833 --> 00:06:16.101
I know about British justice.

61
00:06:16.125 --> 00:06:18.683
You're not allowed to play
both judge and executioner.

62
00:06:18.707 --> 00:06:19.707
Cheerio.

63
00:06:25.957 --> 00:06:27.041
In five…

64
00:06:28.416 --> 00:06:30.351
- In four…
- are you counting down?

65
00:06:30.375 --> 00:06:31.957
Why are you killing my scientists?

66
00:06:33.832 --> 00:06:36.332
- In three…
- handler!

67
00:06:37.332 --> 00:06:38.582
I work through a handler.

68
00:06:40.375 --> 00:06:41.683
And he works for?

69
00:06:41.707 --> 00:06:43.183
Not my place to ask.

70
00:06:43.207 --> 00:06:45.308
Only my place to light
the fuse and walk away.

71
00:06:45.332 --> 00:06:46.416
In two…

72
00:06:47.332 --> 00:06:49.267
I receive instructions.

73
00:06:49.291 --> 00:06:51.207
I'm a hired gun. that is all.

74
00:06:51.957 --> 00:06:53.808
Then you're of no
further use to me. In one.

75
00:06:53.832 --> 00:06:55.707
What the hell are you doing?

76
00:06:56.416 --> 00:06:58.601
I think you'll find I don't
answer to you. mycroft.

77
00:06:58.625 --> 00:07:00.267
We don't torture prisoners. sir.

78
00:07:01.916 --> 00:07:03.642
There are rules. Protocol.

79
00:07:03.666 --> 00:07:07.392
This woman is trying to destroy
me. and I will have my satisfaction.

80
00:07:09.041 --> 00:07:11.392
And you have every right. sir. Every right.

81
00:07:11.416 --> 00:07:13.416
But consider this. if you would.

82
00:07:14.166 --> 00:07:16.606
You're out of favour with the
foreign secretary. are you not?

83
00:07:17.250 --> 00:07:18.976
Do you really wish to alienate him further

84
00:07:19.000 --> 00:07:22.125
by not consulting with him on
such a delicate matter as this?

85
00:07:22.875 --> 00:07:25.892
May I remind you. she is our only link

86
00:07:25.916 --> 00:07:28.250
to whoever is killing your scientists. sir.

87
00:07:31.332 --> 00:07:33.142
I was merely endeavouring
to loosen her lips.

88
00:07:33.166 --> 00:07:34.500
But we are englishmen.

89
00:07:36.041 --> 00:07:38.101
- Has to mean something.
- And in a changing world.

90
00:07:38.125 --> 00:07:41.476
how much do you think you're going
to achieve with your queens bury rules

91
00:07:41.500 --> 00:07:43.291
and your absurd sense of fair play?

92
00:07:48.500 --> 00:07:49.750
Loosen the ropes.

93
00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:28.375
Alas. poor yorick.

94
00:08:29.791 --> 00:08:31.500
I knew him. Horatio.

95
00:09:00.500 --> 00:09:04.416
I'm afraid there's going to have
to be some changes around here.

96
00:09:05.208 --> 00:09:08.601
I'm needed abroad on an expedition.

97
00:09:08.625 --> 00:09:13.642
Mycroft. I have arranged a
government clerkship for you in London.

98
00:09:13.666 --> 00:09:14.666
Thank you. father.

99
00:09:16.708 --> 00:09:17.875
Sherlock…

100
00:09:19.333 --> 00:09:21.416
I know you're not going
to want to hear this. but…

101
00:09:22.208 --> 00:09:25.750
Your mother and I think it's best
if you went to boarding school.

102
00:09:31.250 --> 00:09:33.500
I don't want to leave.

103
00:09:36.165 --> 00:09:37.625
Be strong. my boy.

104
00:09:49.665 --> 00:09:50.750
Mother?

105
00:09:51.583 --> 00:09:52.665
We're here.

106
00:10:03.291 --> 00:10:05.375
You brought me home.

107
00:10:12.041 --> 00:10:13.541
You're safe now.

108
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:26.184
Yes. let's get you sat down

109
00:10:26.208 --> 00:10:27.601
- and I'll light you a fire.
- Hello.

110
00:10:27.625 --> 00:10:29.601
- Who's that?
- No. no. mother. mother.

111
00:10:29.625 --> 00:10:32.684
This is James. James
moriarty. He's a friend of mine.

112
00:10:32.708 --> 00:10:36.559
- Hello.
- I'm so glad. darling.

113
00:10:36.583 --> 00:10:38.891
Sherlock never had any friends.

114
00:10:38.915 --> 00:10:41.083
Really?

115
00:10:42.083 --> 00:10:44.165
Well. it's a pleasure to
meet you. mrs Holmes.

116
00:10:45.208 --> 00:10:47.875
Darling. can you hear that music?

117
00:10:48.540 --> 00:10:49.625
That sound.

118
00:10:53.083 --> 00:10:54.458
That's you!

119
00:11:05.250 --> 00:11:06.684
Bea?

120
00:11:06.708 --> 00:11:08.958
Beatrice!

121
00:11:10.541 --> 00:11:11.916
My darling.

122
00:11:15.333 --> 00:11:16.583
Bea!

123
00:11:22.166 --> 00:11:24.767
You're so beautiful.

124
00:11:24.791 --> 00:11:26.684
Come find me.

125
00:11:29.791 --> 00:11:31.666
Why are you running away from me?

126
00:11:33.583 --> 00:11:36.540
Bea! Where are you running off to?

127
00:11:38.250 --> 00:11:39.559
I want to crown you.

128
00:11:41.833 --> 00:11:44.226
I want to crown you. Come!

129
00:11:47.875 --> 00:11:49.540
Come find me. mummy.

130
00:11:50.125 --> 00:11:51.976
Beatrice!

131
00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:53.351
Bea?

132
00:11:53.375 --> 00:11:54.375
Beatrice?

133
00:11:55.625 --> 00:11:56.790
Perhaps…

134
00:11:57.875 --> 00:11:59.875
Perhaps we should sit
down for a moment. mother.

135
00:12:01.000 --> 00:12:03.750
All right. let's... let's take a seat.

136
00:12:14.375 --> 00:12:17.351
She is absolutely exhausted.

137
00:12:17.375 --> 00:12:20.351
Will you light a fire? She
needs warmth. rest and food.

138
00:12:20.375 --> 00:12:22.708
Yes. Sherlock. where is
your father in all of this?

139
00:12:23.791 --> 00:12:25.601
This shouldn't all be on your shoulders.

140
00:12:25.625 --> 00:12:27.892
He's in Vienna. He's a busy man.

141
00:12:27.916 --> 00:12:32.559
It's all right. I'm here
and I'm dealing with this.

142
00:12:32.583 --> 00:12:34.625
What. by breaking
her out of the asylum?

143
00:12:36.500 --> 00:12:37.976
They were recording her in there. James.

144
00:12:38.000 --> 00:12:40.016
They were listening to
every single word she said.

145
00:12:40.040 --> 00:12:42.601
I had no choice. And
shou'an knew about it.

146
00:12:42.625 --> 00:12:46.141
There's a man with a bird's
claw. He's coming back for me.

147
00:12:46.165 --> 00:12:47.625
How did she know?

148
00:12:50.833 --> 00:12:52.083
Sherlock!

149
00:12:54.500 --> 00:12:55.958
Mother!

150
00:13:02.166 --> 00:13:03.458
Mother!

151
00:13:19.458 --> 00:13:20.666
Mother!

152
00:13:27.208 --> 00:13:29.976
No. no. no. No. no. no.
darling. I have to find her.

153
00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:32.516
- She's sinking. She's sinking.
- She's not here. mother.

154
00:13:32.540 --> 00:13:35.184
- She's sinking! She's sinking!
- She's not! No. she's not! She's gone!

155
00:13:35.208 --> 00:13:36.101
Beatrice!

156
00:13:36.125 --> 00:13:37.516
I need to save her!

157
00:13:37.540 --> 00:13:38.809
Beatrice!

158
00:13:38.833 --> 00:13:40.250
Come on. mother.

159
00:13:49.415 --> 00:13:50.851
Well done.

160
00:13:50.875 --> 00:13:53.016
Right. let's get you warm and dry.

161
00:13:55.165 --> 00:13:58.684
Stop right there. You are not taking her…

162
00:13:58.708 --> 00:14:00.250
Master Holmes!

163
00:14:01.375 --> 00:14:02.458
Crowle.

164
00:14:03.291 --> 00:14:05.934
- I do apologise.
- I heard the commotion.

165
00:14:05.958 --> 00:14:08.309
- Yes.
- Mrs Holmes.

166
00:14:08.333 --> 00:14:11.309
Mr crowle. it's so delightful to see you.

167
00:14:11.333 --> 00:14:13.726
You. too. mrs Holmes.
We weren't expecting you.

168
00:14:13.750 --> 00:14:16.059
Or we would've had the house ready.

169
00:14:16.083 --> 00:14:19.101
Tell me. does dr maltby
still live in the village?

170
00:14:19.125 --> 00:14:20.851
- He does. yes.
- Would you fetch him. please?

171
00:14:20.875 --> 00:14:23.142
- How is mrs crowle?
- She's well. thank you.

172
00:14:23.166 --> 00:14:25.226
Right away. please.
crowle. I rather need his help.

173
00:14:25.250 --> 00:14:26.250
Of course.

174
00:14:32.875 --> 00:14:34.208
For your head.

175
00:14:40.125 --> 00:14:42.500
More trouble than she's worth.

176
00:14:43.040 --> 00:14:46.958
Electric shock has clearly
fried your faculties. philpot.

177
00:14:47.665 --> 00:14:50.583
No cordelia Holmes. no money.

178
00:14:51.208 --> 00:14:53.415
And I rather like money.

179
00:14:55.625 --> 00:14:56.750
Do you follow?

180
00:15:00.500 --> 00:15:02.333
Find her.

181
00:15:03.125 --> 00:15:04.208
And quickly.

182
00:15:05.833 --> 00:15:06.958
As you wish…

183
00:15:08.875 --> 00:15:10.083
Sir.

184
00:15:14.708 --> 00:15:17.458
Razor talons.

185
00:15:18.416 --> 00:15:19.750
Sharp as knives.

186
00:15:20.625 --> 00:15:22.208
So vivid.

187
00:15:23.958 --> 00:15:27.267
Sweetheart. there is nothing you can do.

188
00:15:27.291 --> 00:15:29.976
He is coming back for me.
the man with the bird's claw.

189
00:15:30.000 --> 00:15:32.516
Who is it you're talking
about. mrs Holmes?

190
00:15:34.540 --> 00:15:37.415
Right. stand back. please.
Let's. not crowd the patient.

191
00:15:40.583 --> 00:15:41.833
Hello. cordelia.

192
00:15:43.333 --> 00:15:46.790
Can't tell you how pleased I am to see
you again. even in such circumstances.

193
00:15:47.458 --> 00:15:50.208
But don't you worry. We're
going to get you right as rain.

194
00:15:50.750 --> 00:15:53.809
Do you know what she was
prescribed at the asylum?

195
00:15:53.833 --> 00:15:55.559
Alkaloids. I believe.

196
00:15:55.583 --> 00:15:58.290
Right. yes. Well. she's obviously
suffering from withdrawals.

197
00:15:58.875 --> 00:16:02.392
Perhaps I can give you something
else. something to clear the fog a little.

198
00:16:02.416 --> 00:16:04.142
It's all right. mother.
He's not like the others.

199
00:16:04.166 --> 00:16:05.886
- He's here to help you.
- Right. cordelia.

200
00:16:07.166 --> 00:16:10.500
I want you to take two of
these with some water. please.

201
00:16:13.125 --> 00:16:14.767
Here we go.

202
00:16:14.791 --> 00:16:15.958
Down the hatch.

203
00:16:20.833 --> 00:16:22.684
Your mother's in trouble. Sherlock.

204
00:16:22.708 --> 00:16:23.809
She'll get better.

205
00:16:23.833 --> 00:16:26.625
Yes. I believe that she will. but
that's not what I'm referring to.

206
00:16:27.250 --> 00:16:28.809
Shou'an knows about those recordings.

207
00:16:28.833 --> 00:16:31.059
Now. we don't know whether
she's responsible for them.

208
00:16:31.083 --> 00:16:33.923
but either way. this does connect
your mother to the murders in Oxford.

209
00:16:35.375 --> 00:16:37.790
So how can we say that she's safe here?

210
00:16:38.665 --> 00:16:39.726
We can't.

211
00:16:39.750 --> 00:16:42.500
"The man with the bird's claw."
You have no idea what she means?

212
00:16:46.790 --> 00:16:48.125
My mind is blank.

213
00:16:49.208 --> 00:16:51.434
Well. then maybe it's not a person?

214
00:16:51.458 --> 00:16:54.915
Bird's claw. it's a phrase.
or a place. or a thing.

215
00:17:02.791 --> 00:17:06.391
Perhaps it's some sort
of crest. The bird's claw.

216
00:17:06.415 --> 00:17:10.290
Good. Good. So whose
crest? Someone at the asylum?

217
00:17:10.875 --> 00:17:12.250
Or someone at Oxford.

218
00:17:16.583 --> 00:17:18.165
Sherlock?

219
00:17:19.750 --> 00:17:21.040
I've got nothing.

220
00:17:22.625 --> 00:17:23.976
Perhaps I was wrong.

221
00:17:24.000 --> 00:17:26.016
Words I never thought I'd hear you say.

222
00:17:26.040 --> 00:17:29.833
No. perhaps I was wrong about the crest.
Perhaps it's some other sort of symbol.

223
00:17:31.083 --> 00:17:34.958
The answer to many of life's
problems lie at the bottom of a glass.

224
00:18:21.041 --> 00:18:23.708
I've seen it somewhere.
Where have I seen it?

225
00:18:27.041 --> 00:18:28.291
Bird claw.

226
00:18:35.250 --> 00:18:36.601
It's professor Malik.

227
00:18:36.625 --> 00:18:37.767
Well. go on.

228
00:18:37.791 --> 00:18:41.101
- Professor Malik has a cane.
- Yes.

229
00:18:41.125 --> 00:18:42.767
- And his cane…
- yes?

230
00:18:42.791 --> 00:18:44.291
…has a bird's claw.

231
00:18:45.166 --> 00:18:46.875
All right.

232
00:18:47.666 --> 00:18:49.101
Bravo!

233
00:18:49.125 --> 00:18:51.559
So if I am correct. if it is Malik.

234
00:18:51.583 --> 00:18:55.559
what's his business with my mother?
What's his why? What's his incentive?

235
00:18:55.583 --> 00:18:57.666
Well. shou'an knows
about those recordings.

236
00:18:58.833 --> 00:19:01.666
So perhaps she can answer that.
So perhaps you need to ask her.

237
00:19:03.708 --> 00:19:08.351
I took the Liberty of rustling a
little something up. master Holmes.

238
00:19:08.375 --> 00:19:11.309
I thought you'd be hungry
after the night you've had.

239
00:19:11.333 --> 00:19:14.017
Yes. thank you. mrs crowle.
That's very. very thoughtful.

240
00:19:14.041 --> 00:19:15.892
But we need to pop
into town for a few hours.

241
00:19:15.916 --> 00:19:17.601
so I'll need you to look after my mother.

242
00:19:17.625 --> 00:19:19.750
She'll want for nothing. master Holmes.

243
00:19:21.375 --> 00:19:23.809
There's ammunition in my father's study.

244
00:19:23.833 --> 00:19:26.434
Don't let anyone into this house.

245
00:19:26.458 --> 00:19:27.458
Understood.

246
00:19:28.708 --> 00:19:32.333
And if you need to send word. you
can reach us at Oxford police station.

247
00:19:32.916 --> 00:19:33.916
James?

248
00:19:34.916 --> 00:19:36.791
A man can't think on an empty stomach.

249
00:19:38.125 --> 00:19:39.934
- Thank you. mrs crowle.
- You're welcome.

250
00:19:39.958 --> 00:19:41.434
Thank you. mrs crowle.

251
00:19:41.458 --> 00:19:43.375
Stolen?

252
00:19:45.083 --> 00:19:46.642
Borrowed.

253
00:19:46.666 --> 00:19:48.142
Lovely.

254
00:19:48.166 --> 00:19:49.642
From the asylum.

255
00:19:49.666 --> 00:19:52.392
I'm starting to appreciate
your thieving ways. Sherlock.

256
00:19:52.416 --> 00:19:53.851
Get on!

257
00:19:53.875 --> 00:19:56.041
It's a far cry from a pocket watch.

258
00:20:03.291 --> 00:20:05.583
Would you stop creeping up on me?

259
00:20:06.583 --> 00:20:07.767
Well?

260
00:20:07.791 --> 00:20:08.958
What is it?

261
00:20:11.958 --> 00:20:13.267
You did what?

262
00:20:13.291 --> 00:20:16.726
She is at home and she is safe.
Mrs crowle is looking after her.

263
00:20:16.750 --> 00:20:19.851
They were recording her. mycroft. I
don't know what you expected me to do.

264
00:20:19.875 --> 00:20:23.101
How about not breaking her
out of the asylum. for starters?

265
00:20:23.125 --> 00:20:27.059
How about going one single
day without breaking the law?

266
00:20:27.083 --> 00:20:28.809
Sounds a very disappointing life.

267
00:20:28.833 --> 00:20:30.267
I can't imagine what father's going to say.

268
00:20:30.291 --> 00:20:33.351
I would imagine he'd be pleased
at one of us showing some initiative.

269
00:20:33.375 --> 00:20:35.309
We should wire him.
He could sort this out.

270
00:20:35.333 --> 00:20:36.684
Are you quite well?

271
00:20:36.708 --> 00:20:38.726
Have you fallen down and bumped
your head on something hard?

272
00:20:38.750 --> 00:20:40.684
Professor Malik was at the asylum.

273
00:20:40.708 --> 00:20:44.267
He must have been the one recording
her. Mother gave me a description.

274
00:20:44.291 --> 00:20:45.434
Of him?

275
00:20:45.458 --> 00:20:47.101
Of his cane. The man
with the bird's claw.

276
00:20:47.125 --> 00:20:49.351
- You were there. mycroft.
- Sherlock. she rambles.

277
00:20:49.375 --> 00:20:50.434
There's always an outside chance

278
00:20:50.458 --> 00:20:53.184
she's gonna accidentally
say something half plausible.

279
00:20:53.208 --> 00:20:55.392
- Apis mellifera.
- No. no. no. no.

280
00:20:55.416 --> 00:20:57.392
The honeybees. Yes.
mycroft. The honeybees.

281
00:20:57.416 --> 00:20:59.176
- Yes. I know about the honeybees.
- I don't.

282
00:21:06.666 --> 00:21:10.142
When we were little. we
had a hive. Apis mellifera.

283
00:21:10.166 --> 00:21:13.476
I watched the bees and I told
mycroft that I'd seen them dancing.

284
00:21:13.500 --> 00:21:14.976
And you called me foolish.

285
00:21:15.000 --> 00:21:16.309
"Witless" was the word I used.

286
00:21:16.333 --> 00:21:17.726
I then went and checked with father...

287
00:21:17.750 --> 00:21:21.184
and he said that honeybees
do a little circling dance

288
00:21:21.208 --> 00:21:23.851
- to communicate with each other.
- It's called the tarantella.

289
00:21:23.875 --> 00:21:25.559
And you called me a half-wit.

290
00:21:25.583 --> 00:21:27.750
"Witless" was the word he used.

291
00:21:28.541 --> 00:21:30.767
Well. I wasn't witless.
because I was right.

292
00:21:30.791 --> 00:21:33.267
Glad to see you're not holding
on to a grudge there. Sherlock.

293
00:21:33.291 --> 00:21:35.767
This is the honeybees
all over again. mycroft.

294
00:21:35.791 --> 00:21:39.434
Just because something appears to
be random. it doesn't mean that it is.

295
00:21:39.458 --> 00:21:42.476
Mother said that they were
listening to her. and they were.

296
00:21:42.500 --> 00:21:44.392
She's mentioned the
man with the bird's claw.

297
00:21:44.416 --> 00:21:47.351
Professor Malik has a
cane with a bird's claw.

298
00:21:47.375 --> 00:21:49.958
Yes. but it's not exactly case closed. is it?

299
00:21:50.958 --> 00:21:52.083
Tell me…

300
00:21:54.041 --> 00:21:55.375
Where is professor Malik now?

301
00:21:58.166 --> 00:21:59.809
Well. we are not exactly sure.

302
00:21:59.833 --> 00:22:03.559
He seems to have vanished
after last night's events.

303
00:22:03.583 --> 00:22:05.166
Why would he vanish?

304
00:22:05.666 --> 00:22:07.166
If shou'an is in a cell.

305
00:22:08.375 --> 00:22:09.875
if the threat is gone…

306
00:22:11.916 --> 00:22:13.416
Then why would he vanish?

307
00:22:17.500 --> 00:22:18.708
Yeah.

308
00:22:22.916 --> 00:22:25.166
Ten minutes with shou'an.

309
00:22:26.583 --> 00:22:27.684
No.

310
00:22:27.708 --> 00:22:28.833
Nine minutes.

311
00:22:34.833 --> 00:22:37.059
- Sherlock!
- Mr patton!

312
00:22:37.083 --> 00:22:40.559
- What are you in for this time?
- I'm just visiting today.

313
00:22:40.583 --> 00:22:43.142
Remember. prison is in here.

314
00:22:43.166 --> 00:22:47.476
He's very… I don't know.
mycroft. what's the word?

315
00:22:47.500 --> 00:22:49.333
Bothersome.

316
00:22:50.208 --> 00:22:51.666
Vexatious.

317
00:22:52.250 --> 00:22:54.000
Unbearable.

318
00:22:54.833 --> 00:22:56.059
I could empty the dictionary.

319
00:22:56.083 --> 00:23:00.559
No. no. no. I was
thinking he's very… intense.

320
00:23:03.500 --> 00:23:05.416
How was he like. as a small boy?

321
00:23:06.250 --> 00:23:10.142
Well. growing up in
the same house was…

322
00:23:12.750 --> 00:23:14.458
Yes. I can only imagine.

323
00:23:19.208 --> 00:23:20.583
No. actually. I can't.

324
00:23:22.541 --> 00:23:24.583
- Tell me.
- Put it this way.

325
00:23:25.666 --> 00:23:28.833
I took a job in the foreign
office in pursuit of an easier life.

326
00:23:29.833 --> 00:23:32.958
Wars. famine. that sort of thing.

327
00:23:36.541 --> 00:23:39.142
I wondered when you and I
would be seeing each other again.

328
00:23:39.166 --> 00:23:44.392
I must admit. life has become
somewhat tepid without you.

329
00:23:44.416 --> 00:23:45.476
You mind if I sit?

330
00:23:45.500 --> 00:23:48.125
Please. Take the royal throne.

331
00:23:50.833 --> 00:23:53.500
Thank you. Princess.

332
00:23:57.958 --> 00:23:59.309
What game are we playing today?

333
00:23:59.333 --> 00:24:02.017
- What game would you like to play?
- I'll let you decide.

334
00:24:02.041 --> 00:24:05.726
How very kind. Why don't we start by
you telling me how my mother is involved?

335
00:24:05.750 --> 00:24:09.226
English boys and their mothers.

336
00:24:09.250 --> 00:24:10.684
Very touching.

337
00:24:10.708 --> 00:24:12.892
How did you know what
she said to me in the asylum?

338
00:24:12.916 --> 00:24:16.517
The likeliest explanation
is always the simplest.

339
00:24:16.541 --> 00:24:19.791
The likeliest explanation would
be that you heard her say it.

340
00:24:22.666 --> 00:24:23.833
The recordings.

341
00:24:25.083 --> 00:24:26.142
You had access to them?

342
00:24:26.166 --> 00:24:28.583
Ooh. Lightning fast.

343
00:24:30.375 --> 00:24:31.541
Professor Malik.

344
00:24:32.333 --> 00:24:33.726
Is there a question there?

345
00:24:33.750 --> 00:24:36.226
- Why did he visit my mother?
- How do you know it was him?

346
00:24:36.250 --> 00:24:40.541
"The man with the bird's claw."
Clearly a reference to his walking cane.

347
00:24:42.083 --> 00:24:44.041
That was Malik.

348
00:24:46.041 --> 00:24:48.184
There's a place where I met my handler.

349
00:24:48.208 --> 00:24:49.767
A safe house.

350
00:24:49.791 --> 00:24:51.309
They're listening to me.

351
00:24:51.333 --> 00:24:53.267
A whirring all the time.

352
00:24:53.291 --> 00:24:57.517
There's a man with a bird
claw. He's coming back for me.

353
00:24:57.541 --> 00:24:58.791
This safe house.

354
00:25:00.083 --> 00:25:02.184
do you think it's possible
Malik is still there?

355
00:25:02.208 --> 00:25:05.000
Imagine if we combined our talents.

356
00:25:06.416 --> 00:25:09.041
You want Malik. I want him too.

357
00:25:09.625 --> 00:25:11.166
For very different reasons.

358
00:25:12.666 --> 00:25:15.892
I want to find out why he
was recording my mother.

359
00:25:15.916 --> 00:25:17.541
You. on the other hand.

360
00:25:18.625 --> 00:25:19.625
want to kill him.

361
00:25:21.166 --> 00:25:22.500
Then let's help each other.

362
00:25:23.958 --> 00:25:25.791
The final act we can debate later.

363
00:25:29.791 --> 00:25:31.000
Where is this safe house?

364
00:25:34.125 --> 00:25:36.291
You are going to have
to give up something.

365
00:25:37.750 --> 00:25:41.791
I very much doubt hodge is going
to let you out of here until you do.

366
00:25:42.458 --> 00:25:45.101
But that is preposterous. Slanderous.

367
00:25:45.125 --> 00:25:48.267
Professor Malik works for me. Why
on earth would he be at this... this...

368
00:25:48.291 --> 00:25:50.000
- safe house. sir.
- Safe house.

369
00:25:50.708 --> 00:25:53.875
There is nothing in Malik's file
to suggest any nefarious activity.

370
00:25:54.583 --> 00:25:56.809
- All I know is what I saw.
- I should have hanged you this morning.

371
00:25:56.833 --> 00:25:58.500
- Get her out of here.
- Hold on.

372
00:26:00.583 --> 00:26:02.642
I didn't see him at the gala.

373
00:26:02.666 --> 00:26:04.458
- Who?
- Professor Malik.

374
00:26:05.125 --> 00:26:08.017
When I came through the
wall at the gala. I didn't see him.

375
00:26:08.041 --> 00:26:11.142
All of the other professors were
there at the table. except him.

376
00:26:11.166 --> 00:26:12.208
Yes. but…

377
00:26:14.583 --> 00:26:15.583
He left.

378
00:26:22.083 --> 00:26:23.833
…of her majesty's empire.

379
00:26:24.500 --> 00:26:26.958
Don't take the empire for granted.

380
00:26:27.875 --> 00:26:30.184
We may live to regret it.

381
00:26:30.208 --> 00:26:32.142
During your speech. sir.

382
00:26:32.166 --> 00:26:35.458
I thought it odd at the time. Why
would anyone leave my speech?

383
00:26:36.416 --> 00:26:38.434
I assumed the poor
fellow had bladder issues.

384
00:26:38.458 --> 00:26:40.642
Were you given an exact
time to carry out the explosion?

385
00:26:40.666 --> 00:26:42.351
Eight o'clock.

386
00:26:42.375 --> 00:26:45.184
My instructions were
quite explicit on that point.

387
00:26:45.208 --> 00:26:49.851
Unless Malik had a conveniently
life-saving desire to urinate.

388
00:26:49.875 --> 00:26:52.309
I think it fair to say he knew
the bomb would go off at 8:00.

389
00:26:52.333 --> 00:26:54.517
If he is in this safe house. sir.

390
00:26:54.541 --> 00:26:57.601
and if he is indeed working
against your interests.

391
00:26:57.625 --> 00:26:58.875
wouldn't you rather know?

392
00:27:00.541 --> 00:27:02.059
Let's go. constable.

393
00:27:02.083 --> 00:27:05.017
Front and back doors
are sealed with plate metal.

394
00:27:05.041 --> 00:27:06.934
Bars on the windows half an inch thick.

395
00:27:06.958 --> 00:27:08.476
Basement has a coded lock.

396
00:27:08.500 --> 00:27:10.642
I want an officer by her side at all times.

397
00:27:10.666 --> 00:27:12.184
I'll take Sherlock.

398
00:27:12.208 --> 00:27:14.458
You think she gets to
choose who babysits her?

399
00:27:15.166 --> 00:27:16.934
- No. sir.
- No. sir.

400
00:27:16.958 --> 00:27:18.500
Sherlock or no one.

401
00:27:20.166 --> 00:27:21.392
Or send me back to my cell.

402
00:27:21.416 --> 00:27:24.458
And you can find Malik yourself.

403
00:27:40.625 --> 00:27:42.000
Why are you doing this?

404
00:27:42.583 --> 00:27:44.976
Because there's a
chance it keeps me alive.

405
00:27:45.000 --> 00:27:48.291
No. why are you after Malik?
Why are you killing professors?

406
00:27:49.333 --> 00:27:51.351
It's what I am paid to do.

407
00:27:51.375 --> 00:27:53.166
I don't believe that.

408
00:27:53.750 --> 00:27:54.750
Do you trust me?

409
00:27:55.333 --> 00:27:57.601
Of course I don't trust you.
You know I don't trust you.

410
00:27:59.458 --> 00:28:01.458
And nor I you.

411
00:28:05.250 --> 00:28:06.500
The code is hydra.

412
00:28:07.666 --> 00:28:09.851
Seventeen stars in the southern sky.

413
00:28:48.291 --> 00:28:49.541
All yours.

414
00:28:53.958 --> 00:28:55.166
Don't force my hand.

415
00:28:58.000 --> 00:28:59.916
Right. come on!

416
00:29:01.375 --> 00:29:02.726
Thank you.

417
00:29:02.750 --> 00:29:03.809
No. thank you.

418
00:29:06.166 --> 00:29:07.333
Malik.

419
00:29:33.500 --> 00:29:34.750
Your highness.

420
00:29:35.958 --> 00:29:39.541
May I present to you
the real Princess shou'an.

421
00:29:40.875 --> 00:29:42.726
Your highness. sir bucephalus hodge.

422
00:29:42.750 --> 00:29:47.642
I only wish that our first meeting had
been under more salubrious circumstances.

423
00:29:47.666 --> 00:29:51.142
Trust me when I tell you that I have
spared no expense in my search for you.

424
00:29:51.166 --> 00:29:55.041
O'shea. send a wire immediately
to the foreign secretary.

425
00:29:55.666 --> 00:29:56.916
O'shea…

426
00:29:57.500 --> 00:29:59.642
Be sure to tell him I found her.

427
00:29:59.666 --> 00:30:00.726
Yes. sir.

428
00:30:00.750 --> 00:30:02.958
This is where I saw
professor Malik listening.

429
00:30:08.333 --> 00:30:09.541
Sherlock?

430
00:30:10.500 --> 00:30:11.500
Your mother.

431
00:30:12.250 --> 00:30:14.000
All of her recordings.

432
00:30:26.708 --> 00:30:30.226
I had a little pony. his
name was dapple grey.

433
00:30:30.250 --> 00:30:32.851
I lent him to a lady to ride a mile.

434
00:30:32.875 --> 00:30:37.851
She whipped him and she
slashed him. and she… make it…

435
00:30:37.875 --> 00:30:40.666
Make it stop!

436
00:30:53.083 --> 00:30:54.416
I'm so sorry.

437
00:30:55.333 --> 00:30:57.125
Why would anybody want to do this?

438
00:30:58.375 --> 00:31:01.351
While you were detained
by these nefarious individuals.

439
00:31:01.375 --> 00:31:04.291
did you. by any chance. happen to see…

440
00:31:07.166 --> 00:31:08.333
This man?

441
00:31:09.083 --> 00:31:10.309
No.

442
00:31:10.333 --> 00:31:13.142
You see. I knew he would
never have been embroiled

443
00:31:13.166 --> 00:31:15.059
in this unsavoury business. mycroft.

444
00:31:15.083 --> 00:31:18.017
You see. unlike you. professor Malik
understands the meaning of loyalty.

445
00:31:18.041 --> 00:31:19.851
- Malik?
- Yes.

446
00:31:19.875 --> 00:31:22.226
- You recognise his name?
- Yes. they mentioned him.

447
00:31:22.250 --> 00:31:23.726
- Perhaps you misheard.
- I did not.

448
00:31:23.750 --> 00:31:26.083
Only yesterday they
talked of visiting him.

449
00:31:26.875 --> 00:31:29.934
Your highness. did they say where?

450
00:31:29.958 --> 00:31:32.958
"At abdon. Behind the locks."

451
00:31:34.083 --> 00:31:35.166
That's all I heard.

452
00:31:40.000 --> 00:31:42.666
Sherlock. all of these are
transcripts of the recordings.

453
00:31:44.916 --> 00:31:47.083
Her entire life is laid out in here.

454
00:31:48.375 --> 00:31:52.875
This is a record of her visitors.
Myself. my brother. my father.

455
00:31:55.583 --> 00:31:58.476
There's a "Lawson jaggers". A lawyer.

456
00:31:58.500 --> 00:32:00.601
- Is that someone you know?
- No.

457
00:32:00.625 --> 00:32:02.767
When did jaggers last visit?

458
00:32:02.791 --> 00:32:05.934
Friday. August 11th. 10 o'clock.

459
00:32:05.958 --> 00:32:08.358
Sherlock. that page has been
torn out of the transcriptions.

460
00:32:09.833 --> 00:32:12.226
August 11th. 10 o'clock?

461
00:32:12.250 --> 00:32:13.583
Yes.

462
00:32:19.750 --> 00:32:23.458
Mr jaggers' here to see you.

463
00:32:24.666 --> 00:32:28.601
Mrs Holmes. charming to see you again.

464
00:32:28.625 --> 00:32:30.166
I'll leave you two to talk.

465
00:32:34.875 --> 00:32:37.375
New rooms. I see. Very nice.

466
00:32:38.500 --> 00:32:42.892
Now. perhaps we might continue
with our previous matter of business.

467
00:32:52.375 --> 00:32:53.726
It's been scratched.

468
00:32:53.750 --> 00:32:55.517
- The cylinder. It's…
- sabotaged.

469
00:32:55.541 --> 00:32:57.476
Someone must have been
rather keen to make sure

470
00:32:57.500 --> 00:32:59.226
we don't find out what's on there.

471
00:32:59.250 --> 00:33:01.666
Sherlock. What's all this?

472
00:33:08.958 --> 00:33:12.000
They're recordings of our mother.

473
00:33:13.333 --> 00:33:14.625
All of them.

474
00:33:18.291 --> 00:33:21.142
Why would someone
do this to her. Sherlock?

475
00:33:21.166 --> 00:33:22.642
We are working on that.

476
00:33:22.666 --> 00:33:25.875
We have a lead on the potential
whereabouts of professor Malik.

477
00:33:26.916 --> 00:33:30.434
Obviously. hodge wants
to pursue it himself. but…

478
00:33:30.458 --> 00:33:32.559
- No. you find professor Malik.
- Right.

479
00:33:32.583 --> 00:33:35.517
- You find out why he's been doing this.
- You have my word.

480
00:33:35.541 --> 00:33:38.059
And we will pay a visit to
this Lawson jaggers fellow

481
00:33:38.083 --> 00:33:39.976
and see what business
he's had with our mother.

482
00:33:40.000 --> 00:33:41.500
- Wait. who…
- where is she?

483
00:33:42.333 --> 00:33:45.916
Shou'an. or whatever the hell
her real name is. Where is she?

484
00:33:49.333 --> 00:33:51.892
She... she was here just a moment ago.

485
00:33:51.916 --> 00:33:55.226
Damn you. Holmes. if she's escaped.
you will be held personally responsible.

486
00:33:55.250 --> 00:33:58.226
I have men on all the doors.
There's no way she could have got out.

487
00:33:58.250 --> 00:34:00.875
- How could she have possibly slipped...
- wait.

488
00:34:01.666 --> 00:34:04.976
O'shea. consider
yourself my hunting hound.

489
00:34:05.000 --> 00:34:06.333
Don't bring her back.

490
00:34:22.166 --> 00:34:26.791
This is why she brought us here.
You're an idiot. Holmes. She duped you.

491
00:34:27.750 --> 00:34:29.375
Get out of the way!

492
00:34:30.958 --> 00:34:32.351
Wait! Stop!

493
00:34:35.625 --> 00:34:37.333
Move! Out of the way!

494
00:34:48.791 --> 00:34:49.958
Stop right there!

495
00:35:18.958 --> 00:35:20.976
There is no "abdon" on the map.

496
00:35:21.000 --> 00:35:25.101
She said "behind the locks". Now.
could it be somewhere on the canal?

497
00:35:25.125 --> 00:35:27.184
Could abdon be the name of a boat?

498
00:35:27.208 --> 00:35:29.184
We keep a register of boats
and vessels somewhere.

499
00:35:29.208 --> 00:35:30.642
But where is o'shea?

500
00:35:30.666 --> 00:35:32.434
He hasn't reported back yet. sir.

501
00:35:32.458 --> 00:35:34.351
This is becoming a bloody fiasco!

502
00:35:34.375 --> 00:35:36.726
Find professor Malik. damn it. man!

503
00:35:36.750 --> 00:35:38.976
Thinks he can betray me?
I'll rip his bloody head off!

504
00:35:39.000 --> 00:35:41.101
Might I ask exactly what
the Princess said. sir?

505
00:35:41.125 --> 00:35:45.601
She said they were meeting
professor Malik at abdon.

506
00:35:45.625 --> 00:35:47.000
Behind the locks.

507
00:35:47.625 --> 00:35:48.833
Abdon and sennen.

508
00:35:49.791 --> 00:35:51.208
They're ancient catholic martyrs.

509
00:35:52.333 --> 00:35:53.541
If I may.

510
00:35:54.500 --> 00:35:56.601
There's a ruined medieval
Abbey not far from Oxford.

511
00:35:56.625 --> 00:35:58.392
It was once dedicated to them.

512
00:35:58.416 --> 00:35:59.500
"Behind the locks"?

513
00:36:00.208 --> 00:36:01.291
The locks of Marian.

514
00:36:03.125 --> 00:36:05.833
An old relic believed to
have been kept at the Abbey.

515
00:36:06.541 --> 00:36:09.250
According to legend. it was
the hair of Mary. mother of Jesus.

516
00:36:10.083 --> 00:36:12.017
Well. I never. Edie.
How did you know this?

517
00:36:12.041 --> 00:36:14.416
My father encouraged me to read. sir.

518
00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:18.226
Why don't you know this. mycroft?

519
00:36:18.250 --> 00:36:23.041
A little scratchy on my
esoteric Christian martyrs. sir.

520
00:36:25.541 --> 00:36:27.000
Where is this ruined Abbey?

521
00:36:27.916 --> 00:36:28.976
There. sir.

522
00:36:29.000 --> 00:36:31.125
Shou'an's making a
good habit of beating you.

523
00:36:31.916 --> 00:36:32.916
Nonsense.

524
00:36:33.458 --> 00:36:37.309
As a matter of fact. I think you'll
find I helped her to regain her Liberty.

525
00:36:37.333 --> 00:36:40.059
I see. So you knew
about the passageway?

526
00:36:40.083 --> 00:36:41.267
You knew she was going to escape?

527
00:36:41.291 --> 00:36:45.684
I simply decided the world was a
more interesting place with her in it.

528
00:36:47.916 --> 00:36:49.166
What a load of shite.

529
00:36:56.000 --> 00:36:58.666
Lawson jaggers. esquire.

530
00:37:07.208 --> 00:37:09.208
Smells interesting.

531
00:37:21.250 --> 00:37:22.250
Are you all ready?

532
00:37:27.666 --> 00:37:30.226
There's more than one
way to skin a cat. James.

533
00:37:30.250 --> 00:37:33.250
Well. this is how I like to skin my cats.

534
00:37:52.541 --> 00:37:53.541
Dear lord.

535
00:37:55.458 --> 00:37:57.934
That's the last of jaggers. esquire.

536
00:37:57.958 --> 00:38:00.583
Mrs Holmes. how
charming to see you again.

537
00:38:05.125 --> 00:38:06.267
Is that blood?

538
00:38:09.041 --> 00:38:10.125
Sign of a struggle.

539
00:38:11.625 --> 00:38:12.916
He got in a scrap.

540
00:38:17.750 --> 00:38:20.851
So someone erases his
conversations with my mother.

541
00:38:20.875 --> 00:38:23.642
And then he finds himself
unceremoniously erased.

542
00:38:23.666 --> 00:38:25.875
A rather convenient
suicide. don't you think?

543
00:38:28.375 --> 00:38:31.934
Diaries. Might tell you what
business he had with your mother.

544
00:38:31.958 --> 00:38:33.601
I am going to report this.

545
00:38:33.625 --> 00:38:34.726
To the police?

546
00:38:34.750 --> 00:38:36.476
- Yes.
- And do their jobs for them?

547
00:38:36.500 --> 00:38:39.017
Because I have been
suspected of murder before.

548
00:38:39.041 --> 00:38:40.767
and I would rather it didn't happen again.

549
00:38:40.791 --> 00:38:44.750
Seneca says the problem
with this life is not that it's short.

550
00:38:45.791 --> 00:38:47.871
It's that we waste an
awful lot of it dicking about.

551
00:39:20.416 --> 00:39:22.250
I'd like to report a death.

552
00:39:23.041 --> 00:39:27.726
Lawson jaggers. Solicitor. 4 alba Lane.

553
00:39:27.750 --> 00:39:28.833
And you are?

554
00:39:30.166 --> 00:39:32.416
- Sherlock Holmes.
- Holmes?

555
00:39:33.166 --> 00:39:35.000
We have a wire for you.

556
00:39:37.291 --> 00:39:38.333
Sherlock?

557
00:39:42.333 --> 00:39:43.791
Hyah! Giddyap!

558
00:39:47.000 --> 00:39:48.083
Sherlock.

559
00:39:52.625 --> 00:39:55.250
Let me go!

560
00:39:55.708 --> 00:39:57.767
- Mother?
- Sherlock!

561
00:39:57.791 --> 00:40:00.101
Mother! Get off her!
Unhand her! Unhand her now!

562
00:40:00.125 --> 00:40:03.017
She requires help. She needs to
be somewhere she can be cared for.

563
00:40:03.041 --> 00:40:05.476
I'm so sorry. Sherlock. I
was only gone for a moment.

564
00:40:05.500 --> 00:40:07.267
Don't you worry. crowle. They
won't be taking her anywhere.

565
00:40:07.291 --> 00:40:10.392
I believe you'll find I
have jurisdiction over her.

566
00:40:11.750 --> 00:40:15.000
And I believe you'll find I
have jurisdiction over this.

567
00:40:21.375 --> 00:40:24.458
Is the double-barrel led 12-bore hammer
gun not persuasive enough for you?

568
00:40:27.250 --> 00:40:28.291
- Let her go.
- Thank you.

569
00:40:29.416 --> 00:40:32.125
We're only acting in her best interests.

570
00:40:33.875 --> 00:40:35.416
You knew. didn't you?

571
00:40:36.333 --> 00:40:38.458
You knew about the
recordings. About professor Malik.

572
00:40:41.125 --> 00:40:43.083
- Why did he do it?
- You'll have to ask him.

573
00:40:43.666 --> 00:40:45.266
I was merely paid to look the other way.

574
00:40:47.916 --> 00:40:49.291
I am so sorry. mother.

575
00:40:50.250 --> 00:40:52.583
I'm so sorry. I should never have left you.

576
00:40:53.708 --> 00:40:57.583
Can I respectfully
suggest that ye all fuck off?

577
00:41:14.000 --> 00:41:15.625
Right. move up!

578
00:41:17.875 --> 00:41:20.708
- You're quite sure this is the place?
- Quite sure. sir.

579
00:41:28.666 --> 00:41:30.059
Lestrade. I want it on the record

580
00:41:30.083 --> 00:41:32.851
that I was the one who
blew this case wide open.

581
00:41:32.875 --> 00:41:33.958
Yes. of course. sir.

582
00:41:36.583 --> 00:41:39.125
I think I saw movement
by the church. sir.

583
00:41:46.750 --> 00:41:48.767
I wish to be the one to apprehend him.

584
00:41:48.791 --> 00:41:50.125
Very good. sir.

585
00:42:41.875 --> 00:42:43.434
Good day to you. bucephalus.

586
00:42:43.458 --> 00:42:44.875
Kishore Malik.

587
00:42:46.458 --> 00:42:49.851
So it's true. My very own personal Judas.

588
00:42:49.875 --> 00:42:53.041
There is nothing that can't be
sacrificed in the pursuit of science.

589
00:42:54.500 --> 00:42:56.517
"Knowledge is the wing
wherewith we fly to heaven."

590
00:42:56.541 --> 00:42:59.059
Don't quote the bard at me. sir.

591
00:42:59.083 --> 00:43:01.601
Don't dress up your grubby
greed in noble sentiment.

592
00:43:01.625 --> 00:43:04.041
You were going to sell my
project to the highest bidder.

593
00:43:05.041 --> 00:43:06.708
What was it. I wasn't
paying you enough?

594
00:43:07.291 --> 00:43:09.434
Greed. pure and simple.

595
00:43:09.458 --> 00:43:11.351
As if you stand for anything else.

596
00:43:11.375 --> 00:43:12.916
I stand for queen and country. sir.

597
00:43:13.583 --> 00:43:15.601
To be an englishman is
to win the lottery of life.

598
00:43:15.625 --> 00:43:18.309
Something I remind myself
of each and every day.

599
00:43:18.333 --> 00:43:20.559
Can I help it if I stand
to make the odd penny

600
00:43:20.583 --> 00:43:22.434
from my tireless dedication to the cause?

601
00:43:22.458 --> 00:43:24.226
I did not betray you. sir. for money.

602
00:43:24.250 --> 00:43:27.958
I betrayed you because what I
discovered could change the world entirely.

603
00:43:29.625 --> 00:43:33.541
And I couldn't bear to see you
take credit for my discoveries.

604
00:43:34.208 --> 00:43:36.392
- For history to forget me.
- But it will. sir.

605
00:43:36.416 --> 00:43:38.351
I will go down as the
man who built the empire.

606
00:43:38.375 --> 00:43:41.015
You. on the other hand. will be
forgotten even by your own mother.

607
00:43:44.000 --> 00:43:47.166
Just one request. before I bid you adieu.

608
00:43:49.291 --> 00:43:51.916
I mean. if you'd be so accommodating.
who did you betray me for?

609
00:43:52.833 --> 00:43:54.226
The prussians?

610
00:43:54.250 --> 00:43:55.583
Ottomans?

611
00:43:57.125 --> 00:44:01.500
Take your hand out of your pocket. man.

612
00:44:10.166 --> 00:44:11.392
Hodge?

613
00:44:11.416 --> 00:44:12.708
Hodge!

614
00:44:17.583 --> 00:44:19.833
Right. fan out! Malik can't have gone far.

615
00:44:24.041 --> 00:44:25.101
Has he been shot?

616
00:44:27.000 --> 00:44:29.291
There's-there's… there's no blood. …

617
00:44:30.916 --> 00:44:32.767
There's no bullet hole. Nothing.

618
00:44:32.791 --> 00:44:34.041
Sir bucephalus?

619
00:44:37.958 --> 00:44:39.958
He's not... he's not breathing.

620
00:44:43.541 --> 00:44:44.958
He's dead.

621
00:44:50.708 --> 00:44:52.000
Guns and hot toddies.

622
00:44:52.583 --> 00:44:54.958
Jesus. you're a woman after
my own heart. mrs crowle.

623
00:44:56.625 --> 00:44:57.708
Mrs crowle.

624
00:44:58.750 --> 00:44:59.976
Thank you.

625
00:45:00.000 --> 00:45:01.541
You're welcome.

626
00:45:04.333 --> 00:45:06.934
Must have felt very good. that slap.

627
00:45:06.958 --> 00:45:08.791
James.

628
00:45:10.541 --> 00:45:13.333
It was such a tonic.

629
00:45:14.125 --> 00:45:15.208
So. what now?

630
00:45:16.958 --> 00:45:21.166
We're still no closer to figuring out
why you were involved in any of this.

631
00:45:24.166 --> 00:45:26.726
The likeliest explanation
is always the simplest.

632
00:45:29.833 --> 00:45:31.833
I was merely paid to look the other way.

633
00:45:41.375 --> 00:45:42.375
Darling.

634
00:45:47.958 --> 00:45:49.166
Sherlock.

635
00:45:49.958 --> 00:45:53.517
My boy. I heard you had a spot of bother.

635
00:45:54.305 --> 00:46:54.936
